criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Be suffering from essential hypertension;

          -  Be properly prescribed medication and have difficulty controlling blood pressure
             keeping regular measurement above was over 140x90 mmHg.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  A woman in pregnancy;

          -  Be in possession of any type of cancer;

          -  being a smoker;

          -  be alcoholic;

          -  Be in drug treatment for other diseases including obesity;

          -  Not dieting for weight loss;

          -  practice regular physical activity.
